86
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:34,448 line:-2
All right.
Let's get started.


87
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,984 line:-2
As I mentioned earlier,
tutorials are


88
00:03:37.017 --> 00:03:39.052 line:-2 align:center
a highly-interactive
way to learn.


89
00:03:39.086 --> 00:03:41.655 line:-2 align:center
And like article
and reference documentation,


90
00:03:41,688 --> 00:03:44,424 line:-2
the text of tutorials
is authored in markdown,


91
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,627 line:-2
but tutorials use
a special syntax


92
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,462 line:-2
to wrap this markdown
in a directive


93
00:03:48,495 --> 00:03:49,897 line:-1
that provides structure


94
00:03:49.930 --> 00:03:52.065 line:-2 align:center
so DocC
can build the complex layout


95
00:03:52.099 --> 00:03:54.034 line:-2 align:center
and interactions
featured in the tutorial.


96
00:03:55,202 --> 00:03:58,205 line:-2
This is a basic directive
that tells DocC


97
00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:01,208 line:-2
this text is a single step
of a tutorial.


98
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:04,011 line:-2
Along with the instructive text,
this example includes a link


99
00:04:04,044 --> 00:04:07,047 line:-2
to a Swift file that DocC
will display to show readers


100
00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:09.716 line:-2 align:center
exactly what code to write
to accomplish the step.


101
00:04:11.151 --> 00:04:13.120 line:-2 align:center
And DocC directives
can be nested.


102
00:04:13.153 --> 00:04:16.456 line:-2 align:center
In this case, the code directive
contains an image directive


103
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,760 line:-2
that provides the reader
more context for the step.


104
00:04:21.361 --> 00:04:23.931 line:-2 align:center
Tutorial pages have lots of
individual steps,


105
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:25,199 line:-1
like the one we just looked at.


106
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:27,935 line:-2
The table of contents
provides organization


107
00:04:27.968 --> 00:04:30.137 line:-2 align:center
and links to the individual
tutorials.


108
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:31,805 line:-2
Let's take a look at
the directives


109
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:33,440 line:-1
of a table of contents.


110
00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:37.344 line:-1 align:center
The table of contents file


111
00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:39,213 line:-2
starts with
a Tutorials directive,


112
00:04:39,246 --> 00:04:41,348 line:-2
which contains all the elements
of the page.


113
00:04:42,516 --> 00:04:45,485 line:-2
Inside the Tutorials directive,
there is an Intro directive,


114
00:04:45.519 --> 00:04:48.422 line:-2 align:center
which includes a title
and a brief description


115
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:50,257 line:-2
of what the framework adopter
will build


116
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,725 line:-1
throughout the tutorials.


117
00:04:53,093 --> 00:04:55,596 line:-2
DocC generates some elements
of the introduction,


118
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:57,064 line:-1
such as the "Get Started" button


119
00:04:57.097 --> 00:04:59.166 line:-2 align:center
and timing calculation
automatically


120
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,801 line:-2
when you provide links
to the tutorials


121
00:05:00,834 --> 00:05:02,703 line:-1
in the Table of Contents page.


122
00:05:04.104 --> 00:05:06.840 line:-2 align:center
The introduction also contains
an image directive.


123
00:05:06,874 --> 00:05:08,242 line:-1
You can store images


124
00:05:08,275 --> 00:05:11,445 line:-2
in your documentation catalog
resources folder.


125
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:14,414 line:-2
Down the page,
you'll find a Chapter directive.


126
00:05:14,448 --> 00:05:16,583 line:-2
You use chapters to organize
tutorials


127
00:05:16,617 --> 00:05:18,252 line:-2
into groups that make sense
together.


128
00:05:18.585 --> 00:05:21.688 line:-2 align:center
Chapters give framework adopters
a clear sense of progress


129
00:05:21,722 --> 00:05:24,491 line:-2
as they follow your tutorials,
as well as provide context


130
00:05:24,525 --> 00:05:26,093 line:-2
for what a framework
is all about.


131
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:28,962 line:-1
Inside the Chapter,


132
00:05:28.996 --> 00:05:31.265 line:-2 align:center
there are individual links
to tutorials.


133
00:05:31.298 --> 00:05:33.400 line:-2 align:center
With all the context set
by this page,


134
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,702 line:-2
framework adopters should
have a good understanding


135
00:05:35.736 --> 00:05:38.105 line:-2 align:center
for what the framework is
and what they'll build with it


136
00:05:38.138 --> 00:05:40.274 line:-2 align:center
before navigating
to a Tutorial page.


137
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:44,378 line:-2
Much like the table of contents,
the Tutorial page starts


138
00:05:44,411 --> 00:05:45,612 line:-1
with a single directive


139
00:05:45,646 --> 00:05:47,347 line:-2
that contains
the contents of the page.


140
00:05:47.381 --> 00:05:51.084 line:-2 align:center
In this case, it's
a single Tutorial directive.


141
00:05:52,019 --> 00:05:55,556 line:-2
DocC uses some information
from the Table of Contents page


142
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:58,525 line:-2
in the tutorial introduction,
letting folks know


143
00:05:58.559 --> 00:06:00.460 line:-2 align:center
what the overall theme
of this tutorial is


144
00:06:00,494 --> 00:06:02,563 line:-2
by referencing the chapter
it belongs to.


145
00:06:03.764 --> 00:06:07.134 line:-2 align:center
The introduction to the tutorial
includes a title and description


146
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:08,569 line:-1
that tell the framework adopter


147
00:06:08.602 --> 00:06:09.937 line:-2 align:center
which part the framework
they'll use


148
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:11,405 line:-1
and what they'll build with it.


149
00:06:11.438 --> 00:06:14.174 line:-2 align:center
To provide clarity
along the path of building,


150
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:16,510 line:-2
tutorials
are broken up into sections.


151
00:06:16.543 --> 00:06:18.612 line:-2 align:center
Section introductions
are very similar


152
00:06:18,645 --> 00:06:20,113 line:-1
to tutorial introductions,


153
00:06:20.147 --> 00:06:22.816 line:-2 align:center
but are specific to progress
the framework adopter will make


154
00:06:22,850 --> 00:06:24,785 line:-2
before moving on
to the next section.


155
00:06:26.086 --> 00:06:28.055 line:-1 align:center
Sections contain steps,


156
00:06:28.088 --> 00:06:31.291 line:-2 align:center
which instruct the adopter
on what exactly they need to do


157
00:06:31.325 --> 00:06:33.493 line:-1 align:center
to move on to the next step.


158
00:06:33.527 --> 00:06:35.863 line:-2 align:center
Steps should be short,
easy to understand,


159
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:37,564 line:-1
and easy to follow.


160
00:06:38,832 --> 00:06:41,235 line:-2
Framework adopters rely on
consistent


161
00:06:41.268 --> 00:06:43.937 line:-2 align:center
and clear tutorial steps
to help them get up-to-speed


162
00:06:43.971 --> 00:06:46.039 line:-2 align:center
on the framework
they're learning about quickly.


163
00:06:46.073 --> 00:06:48.709 line:-2 align:center
It's easier to create
a cohesive set of steps


164
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:50,344 line:-2
throughout a collection
of tutorials


165
00:06:50.377 --> 00:06:52.479 line:-1 align:center
if you start with a clear plan.


166
00:06:52.513 --> 00:06:54.515 line:-2 align:center
Let me show you
how I make this plan


167
00:06:54.548 --> 00:06:56.950 line:-2 align:center
by outlining a collection
of developer tutorials


168
00:06:56,984 --> 00:06:59,453 line:-1
for our new Sloth framework.


169
00:06:59.486 --> 00:07:02.122 line:-2 align:center
In order to understand
how to outline a framework,


170
00:07:02.155 --> 00:07:04.491 line:-2 align:center
it's best to think
about how the framework works


171
00:07:04,525 --> 00:07:06,426 line:-2
and what the real-world uses
are for it.


172
00:07:06.460 --> 00:07:09.162 line:-2 align:center
Now, the framework my colleagues
and I have been working on


173
00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:11.365 line:-2 align:center
is all about sloths,
and it provides quite a bit


174
00:07:11,398 --> 00:07:14,034 line:-2
of cool functionality
I'm excited to see people use.


175
00:07:15.235 --> 00:07:16.270 line:-1 align:center
Here's a high-level view


176
00:07:16,303 --> 00:07:18,205 line:-2
of the main functionality
in the framework.


177
00:07:18,238 --> 00:07:20,274 line:-2
In order to outline my
tutorials,


178
00:07:20,307 --> 00:07:22,409 line:-2
I'm going to list the most
important API


179
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,744 line:-1
so I can get a good idea


180
00:07:23,777 --> 00:07:25,646 line:-2
of how to explain them
through tutorials.


181
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:29,183 line:-2
You can see there's API
like the Sloth type itself,


182
00:07:29,516 --> 00:07:31,885 line:-2
as well as a Food Generator
and PowerPicker.


183
00:07:31.919 --> 00:07:34.221 line:-2 align:center
If I try to think about these
all at once,


184
00:07:34.254 --> 00:07:35.856 line:-2 align:center
it's going to be tricky
to decide


185
00:07:35.889 --> 00:07:37.724 line:-2 align:center
how I should teach them
in a clear order.


186
00:07:37,758 --> 00:07:40,594 line:-2
So let me group them
by general functional area.


187
00:07:42.229 --> 00:07:44.164 line:-2 align:center
I know understanding the
Sloth type is really important


188
00:07:44.198 --> 00:07:45.732 line:-2 align:center
for the adopters of this
framework,


189
00:07:45,766 --> 00:07:47,768 line:-2
so I'll group everything related
to creating


190
00:07:47.801 --> 00:07:49.403 line:-1 align:center
and editing the Sloth type.


191
00:07:49,436 --> 00:07:51,338 line:-1
APIs used for generating sloths,


192
00:07:51.371 --> 00:07:53.407 line:-2 align:center
giving them names,
editing their powers:


193
00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:56.577 line:-2 align:center
these are the core API used
for creating sloths.


194
00:07:57.644 --> 00:08:00.881 line:-2 align:center
And it turns out, the remaining
API, like food generator,


195
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:03,851 line:-2
care schedule, and habitat,
are all related, as well.


196
00:08:03.884 --> 00:08:06.653 line:-2 align:center
These API
about taking care of sloths.


197
00:08:08.021 --> 00:08:10.657 line:-2 align:center
So, it looks like I have two
main API groupings


198
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:11,792 line:-1
that make up the framework:


199
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:14,394 line:-2
the group of API
that are about creating sloths


200
00:08:14,428 --> 00:08:16,897 line:-2
and the group of API that
are about caring for sloths.


201
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:18,565 line:-1
This is a great start.


202
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:21,301 line:-2
I know that adopters will need
to understand these API


203
00:08:21.335 --> 00:08:23.270 line:-2 align:center
to successfully use our
framework.


204
00:08:24,338 --> 00:08:26,874 line:-2
And grouping them in this way
will make it easy for me


205
00:08:26.907 --> 00:08:29.209 line:-2 align:center
to show them how they function
together.


206
00:08:29,243 --> 00:08:31,512 line:-2
But I also know that adopters
of this framework are likely


207
00:08:31.545 --> 00:08:34.281 line:-2 align:center
to want to do more complicated
things in their own apps.


208
00:08:35.482 --> 00:08:37.050 line:-1 align:center
So, I'll add another group.


209
00:08:37,084 --> 00:08:40,053 line:-2
Our new framework is all about
creating and caring for sloths,


210
00:08:40.087 --> 00:08:42.289 line:-2 align:center
but I want to prepare folks
to use it in ways


211
00:08:42,322 --> 00:08:44,291 line:-2
that go beyond the API
it includes,


212
00:08:44.324 --> 00:08:46.159 line:-2 align:center
so I should include
some information


213
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:48,228 line:-1
about interoperability.


214
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:51,164 line:-2
I think adopters are likely to
use the framework to help sloths


215
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:54,168 line:-2
interact with other animals,
move around different locations,


216
00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:56.136 line:-1 align:center
or hang out in groups of sloths.


217
00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:58.405 line:-2 align:center
I'm not trying to imagine
every use case.


218
00:08:58.438 --> 00:09:00.874 line:-2 align:center
I just want enough variety
to introduce folks


219
00:09:00,908 --> 00:09:03,744 line:-2
to ways they might use
the framework in their own apps.


220
00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:06.580 line:-1 align:center
With these three groups,


221
00:09:06.613 --> 00:09:09.149 line:-2 align:center
I have a great start
organizing my tutorials.


222
00:09:09,183 --> 00:09:11,852 line:-2
For now, I'll turn these groups
into chapters,


223
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:14,021 line:-2
and I'll use them
